Bust of Winslow Homer

William R. O' Donovan

American Art

On View: Luce Visible Storage and Study Center, 5th Floor

MEDIUM Bronze

DATES 1876, cast ca. 1911

DIMENSIONS 12 x 6 x 4 1/2 in. (30.5 x 15.2 x 11.4 cm) (show scale)

MARKINGS Foundry mark inscribed on back edge of base: "ROMAN BRONZE WORKS N.Y"

SIGNATURE Inscribed on back of bust: "W.R. O'DONOVAN / © / '81"

INSCRIPTIONS Inscribed on front of bust, below chest: "HOMER"

COLLECTIONS American Art

ACCESSION NUMBER 24.429

CREDIT LINE Museum Collection Fund

CATALOGUE DESCRIPTION Bust portrait of a man truncated below chest and at shoulders; man looks straight ahead with hair combed towards forehead and moustache; smooth and polished surface; bust attached to a round, pedestal base. Condition: Good.

MUSEUM LOCATION This item is on view in Luce Visible Storage and Study Center, 5th Floor

CAPTION William R. O' Donovan (American, 1844–1920). Bust of Winslow Homer, 1876, cast ca. 1911. Bronze, 12 x 6 x 4 1/2 in. (30.5 x 15.2 x 11.4 cm). Brooklyn Museum, Museum Collection Fund, 24.429. Creative Commons-BY (Photo: Brooklyn Museum, 24.429_acetate_bw.jpg)

IMAGE overall, 24.429_acetate_bw.jpg. Brooklyn Museum photograph
